**Wazuh Server Installation**
Step 1: Install Docker on Ubuntu
# Add Docker's official GPG key:
sudo apt-get update
sudo apt-get install ca-certificates curl
sudo install -m 0755 -d /etc/apt/keyrings
sudo curl -fsSL https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu/gpg -o /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc
sudo chmod a+r /etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc

# Add the repository to Apt sources:
echo \
  "deb [arch=$(dpkg --print-architecture) signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/docker.asc] https://download.docker.com/linux/ubuntu \
  $(. /etc/os-release && echo "${UBUNTU_CODENAME:-$VERSION_CODENAME}") stable" | \
  sudo tee /etc/apt/sources.list.d/docker.list > /dev/null
sudo apt-get update

You can copy/paste the commands into a .sh script to run it automatically.
sudo apt-get install docker-ce docker-ce-cli containerd.io docker-buildx-plugin docker-compose-plugin

Verify with: sudo docker run hello-world

Clone Wazuh Server Repository:
git clone https://github.com/wazuh/wazuh-docker.git -b v4.12.0

Inside the single-node folder, geenrate the certs required:
docker-compose -f generate-indexer-certs.yml run --rm generator

Start docker instance: sudo docker compose up -d

**Wazuh Agent Installation for Windows**
On Windows Powershell (Run ad Admin):
Download Agent Installer: Invoke-WebRequest -Uri "https://packages.wazuh.com/4.x/windows/wazuh-agent-4.12.0-1.msi?raw=1" -OutFile "$env:TEMP\wazuh-agent.msi"
Install the MSI: msiexec.exe /i "C:\Users\qothr\Downloads\wazuh-agent.msi" WAZUH_MANAGER="<your-wazuh-manager>" WAZUH_AGENT_NAME="SANDEVISTAN-HOST"
Verify Agent:
- Get-Service OssecSvc
- Get-ChildItem "C:\Program Files (x86)\ossec-agent"





